cs.DC, cs.MS, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on extending task parallel programming to distributed memory systems, which is a key topic in this field.
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation and performance of two mathematical applications.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new programming model for distributed task parallel computing, which can be seen as a software engineering problem.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as the paper introduces a new programming model for parallel computing.
- cs.PF (Performance) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper compares the performance of their implementation with other frameworks for distributed task parallel programming.
